First describe the spiral in terms of coordinates.  
Put 1 at the origin (0, 0).  
If (x, y) is a cell, let  

 k = max(|x|, |y|)                (layer number)  
 s = 2k+1                         (side length)  
 m = s²                           (largest number on the layer, found at (k, –k))

The numbers run counter-clockwise round the square.  
For a point on the layer k the distance d (how far we have moved from m) and thus the value n = m – d are obtained as follows.

bottom edge   (y = –k):       d = k – x  
left   edge   (x = –k):       d = (s–1)+y+k  
top    edge   (y =  k):       d = 2(s–1)+x+k  
right  edge   (x =  k):       d = 3(s–1)+k–y   (y>–k)

--------------------------------------------------------------------
1.  Locate 2026  
The greatest odd square not exceeding 2026 is 45² = 2025, so 2025 is the bottom-right corner of layer k = 22 (because 2k+1 = 45 → k = 22) and is at (22, –22).

2026 is the next number of the spiral, i.e. one step to the right, so  
2026 is at (23, –22).  
Hence its eight neighbours are the cells

(22, –23)   (23, –23)   (24, –23)  
(22, –22)   ——2026——  (24, –22)  
(22, –21)   (23, –21)   (24, –21)

--------------------------------------------------------------------
2.  Evaluate every neighbour

Layer-23 constants:  s = 47, m = 2209, s–1 = 46  
Layer-22 constants:  s = 45, m = 2025, s–1 = 44  
Layer-24 constants:  s = 49, m = 2401, s–1 = 48  

(22, –23): bottom edge of k = 23 → d = 23–22 = 1 → 2209–1  = 2208  
(23, –23): bottom-right of k = 23                →         = 2209  
(24, –23): right edge of k = 24 → d = 3·48+24–(–23)=191 → 2401–191 = 2210  
(22, –22): bottom-right of k = 22                →         = 2025  
(24, –22): right edge of k = 24 → d = 144+24–(–22)=190 → 2401–190 = 2211  
(22, –21): right edge of k = 22 → d = 132+22–(–21)=175 → 2025–175 = 1850  
(23, –21): right edge of k = 23 → d = 138+23–(–21)=182 → 2209–182 = 2027  
(24, –21): right edge of k = 24 → d = 144+24–(–21)=189 → 2401–189 = 2212

--------------------------------------------------------------------
3.  Sum of the eight neighbours

2208 + 2209 + 2210 + 2025 + 2211 + 1850 + 2027 + 2212 
= 16 952

--------------------------------------------------------------------
Answer: 16 952
